laboratory_examinations.procedure_name: CT Abdomen and Pelvis with Contrast

findings.lower_chest: Mild, dependent atelectasis. No pleural or pericardial effusion.
findings.liver: The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout. Subtle hypodensity within the left hepatic lobe may be perfusional.
findings.pancreas: Normal attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions or pancreatic ductal dilatation.
findings.kidneys: Normal and symmetric size with normal nephrogram. No evidence of solid renal lesions or hydronephrosis.
findings.small_bowel: Demonstrate normal caliber, wall thickness, and enhancement throughout.
findings.colon: Colonic diverticulosis, without evidence of acute diverticulitis.
findings.appendix: Mildly dilated to approximately 7-8 mm, with subtle adjacent periappendiceal fat stranding and mild hyperemia of the wall.
findings.nodes: Multiple mildly enlarged, likely reactive nodes in the right lower quadrant along the ileocolic vessels, measuring up to 8 mm short axis.
findings.pelvis: Bladder decompressed, limiting evaluation. No free fluid in the pelvis.
findings.reproductive_organs: Fibroid uterus. An IUD is in place. No adnexal masses.
findings.vascular: No abdominal aortic aneurysm. No atherosclerotic disease seen.
findings.bones: No evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
findings.soft_tissues: Abdominal and pelvic wall is within normal limits.
